					<description><![CDATA[<p>AlphaSense has officially closed a $350 million funding round, and this has almost doubled the company&#8217;s valuation, from $4 billion to $7.5 billion, and taken the total capital raised by</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/alphasense-raises-350m-at-7-5b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">AlphaSense Raises $350M at $7.5B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.alpha-sense.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">AlphaSense </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has officially closed a $350 million </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/firstclub-raises-55m-in-series-b-led-by-peak-xv-sofina/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round, and this has almost doubled the company&#8217;s valuation, from $4 billion to $7.5 billion, and taken the total capital raised by the company to over $1 billion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The huge round was led by the triumvirate of Vitruvian Partners, Accenture Ventures and J. P. Morgan Asset Management. The syndicate was strengthened by two new institutional investors, D. E. Shaw Ventures and Pinegrove Opportunity Partners, and maintained by old stalwarts CapitalG (the independent growth fund of Alphabet), Goldman Sachs Alternatives and Viking Global Investors.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">AI Dominance Met With Hyper-Growth Financials</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $7.5 billion valuation represents the explosive growth of AlphaSense as companies rush to implement trustworthy, vertical, specific AIs. In Q1 2026, the firm announced that its ARR had exceeded $600 million, ticking up from the $500 million ARR landmark it achieved in October 2025.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Where horizontal AI search tools scrape the public web, AlphaSense has built a walled garden of decision-grade intelligence. Its engine indexes over 500 million premium business documents, including exclusive broker research, expert call transcripts from its Tegus acquisition, corporate filings, and earnings call commentary.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202434" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202434" class="size-large wp-image-202434" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/AI-2-1024x578.jpg" alt="AI" width="1024" height="578" /><p id="caption-attachment-202434" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Trusted data is the foundational currency of the modern enterprise,&#8221; said Manish Sharma, Chief Strategy and Services Officer at Accenture, commenting on the deal. &#8220;By integrating AlphaSense&#8217;s &#8216;always-on&#8217; market intelligence with Accenture&#8217;s deep AI expertise, we are empowering clients to move beyond information processing to true enterprise intelligence.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/firstclub-raises-55m-in-series-b-led-by-peak-xv-sofina/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">FirstClub Raises $55M in Series B Led by Peak XV, Sofina</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Shifting Gears into Agentic Workflows</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The capital influx coincides with a major product milestone: the official rollout of SuperAnalyst, AlphaSense&#8217;s new always-on AI execution layer.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The launch represents a structural shift from passive search and synthesis into active autonomous execution. Most corporate investment and strategy teams spend hours tracking market changes, compiling data across fragmented systems, and building research binders manually. SuperAnalyst operates as a secure, background AI assistant designed to execute complex, multi-step research workflows automatically.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Crucially for the compliance-heavy financial sector, the system utilizes a token-efficient architecture that keeps all outputs directly tied and cited to verified sources. This allows analysts, hedge funds, and corporate strategy teams to instantly cross-examine and defend the data backing high-stakes financial decisions.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Aggressive Enterprise Scale and Global Expansion</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">AlphaSense plans to weaponise the $350 million across three core areas:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Product &amp; Content Expansion:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Accelerating the development of its agentic workflow pipeline and continuing to acquire high-value proprietary business content.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Strategic Commercial Alliances:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Leveraging Accenture’s newly minted role as a primary strategic channel partner to scale custom enterprise intelligence systems directly to corporate client networks.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Global Footprint Expansion:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Scaling regional customer support organisations and taking advantage of the newly doubled headcount in EMEA and APAC.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company&#8217;s enterprise adoption has already reached a massive scale, serving more than 7,000 worldwide corporate customers. The list comprises the majority of Fortune 500, close to 90% of the S&amp;P 100, almost all big global investment banks, and 92% of the globe&#8217;s 50 biggest pharma companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To anchor this massive operational scale, the company recently moved into its brand-new global headquarters located at Hudson Yards in New York City, solidifying its status as an absolute powerhouse in the enterprise AI landscape.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/alphasense-raises-350m-at-7-5b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">AlphaSense Raises $350M at $7.5B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
