		<title>Shifters Raises $10.2M to Advance Autonomous Robots</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/shifters-raises-10-2m-to-advance-autonomous-robots/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 14:12:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=202424</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Shifters has raised $10.2 million in seed funding to accelerate the company&#8217;s &#8220;Robots Go First&#8221; mission: building supervised autonomous ground robotic teams designed to extend human reach, optimise situational awareness,</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/shifters-raises-10-2m-to-advance-autonomous-robots/" data-wpel-link="internal">Shifters Raises $10.2M to Advance Autonomous Robots</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.shiftersai.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Shifters </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has raised $10.2 million in seed </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/firstclub-raises-55m-in-series-b-led-by-peak-xv-sofina/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">to accelerate the company&#8217;s &#8220;Robots Go First&#8221; mission: building supervised autonomous ground robotic teams designed to extend human reach, optimise situational awareness, and preserve human life in highly dangerous environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round was led by Ace Capital Partners, a venture firm specialising in defence and dual-use autonomy. A robust syndicate of deep-tech and national security investors also backed the round, including Aurelius Capital Management, Corner Ventures, Arkin Capital, STEP World, and Fresh Fund. This latest round brings Shifters&#8217; total capitalisation to $15 million since its inception.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Ground Autonomy Challenge</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2023 by CEO Ofer Ballin and CTO Assaf Chaprak (a former major in the Israeli Air Force), Shifters was built to address a massive operational vulnerability. Due to the introduction of autonomous aerial drones, modern reconnaissance and defence strategies have been transformed, but ground-level operations remain notoriously difficult, unpredictable, and hazardous.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">When military units, emergency responders, or industrial inspectors encounter collapsed rubble, subterranean tunnels, GPS-denied environments, or hazardous material zones, they are frequently forced to send human personnel first to gain visibility. Shifters is changing that reality by building highly coordinated, quadrupedal (four-legged) robotic teams that can navigate extreme physical obstacles before human teams set foot into danger.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202425" style="width: 423px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202425" class="wp-image-202425" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Shifters.jpg" alt="Shifters" width="413" height="86" /><p id="caption-attachment-202425" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Shifters</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;We&#8217;ve arrived at an era where it&#8217;s finally technologically feasible to take people out of harm&#8217;s way and allow robots to go first,&#8221; said co-founder and CTO Assaf Chaprak. &#8220;The challenge isn&#8217;t simply building a robot that can walk. It&#8217;s a dual hardware and software problem: enabling a team of robots to seamlessly navigate chaotic environments while keeping the human supervision interface simple and intuitive.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News:</span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/firstclub-raises-55m-in-series-b-led-by-peak-xv-sofina/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400"> FirstClub Raises $55M in Series B Led by Peak XV, Sofina</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Three Pillars of the Shifters Ecosystem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Rather than relying on single, isolated pieces of hardware, Shifters has engineered a comprehensive three-part proprietary ecosystem that blends agentic AI with modular physical design:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>TRUST:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> This is the company’s signature family of quadrupedal robotic platforms. Visually resembling rugged, high-tech robotic dogs, the platforms utilise a payload-agnostic layout. Described by the founders as &#8220;a tray with legs&#8221;, the heavy-duty chassis allows operators to easily swap or mount different mission-specific tools, such as cameras, mapping sensors, or hazardous material scanners.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>RITA:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> The software brain and command layer of the ecosystem. This is powered by advanced agentic AI, and it enables the robotic teams to interpret human intent, dynamically adapt to shifting field conditions, and coordinate tasks autonomously without requiring micro-management from a human pilot.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>DIGITAL TWIN:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> This is a high-fidelity virtual simulation and analysis tool which mirrors the exact physical robots, environments, and active missions in a virtual space, allowing operators to run predictive mission profiles, assess risk, and analyse sensor data in real-time.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By using a Modular Open Systems Approach (MOSA) and robust APIs, Shifters ensures that its technology can easily integrate with third-party software and existing military or commercial backend infrastructure.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Scaling Up Production for Global Demand</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Shifters has spent the last three years in deep research and development, continuously field-testing its systems alongside active defence and national security agencies, including units within the United States Army. Following successful demonstrations of coordinated robotic entry and complex tactical navigation, the company is seeing unprecedented demand from both government and enterprise buyers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The newly secured $10.2 million will be weaponised to transition the company from low-rate prototyping into full-scale commercial manufacturing. Shifters plan to establish new manufacturing lines capable of churning out hardware at scale, refine the copilot-style autonomous capabilities of the RITA software layer, and aggressively grow its corporate and engineering footprint across the United States, Europe, and the Middle East.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) missions represent the immediate go-to-market driver for Shifters, the company notes that its platform is naturally suited for a broad array of high-risk commercial applications. These include critical infrastructure inspections, underground mining operations, search-and-rescue tasks following natural disasters, and precision agriculture.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/shifters-raises-10-2m-to-advance-autonomous-robots/" data-wpel-link="internal">Shifters Raises $10.2M to Advance Autonomous Robots</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
